Package: wsl.gbif
Type: Package
Title: A toolbox to efficiently download and filter large GBIF observational datasets for sound spatial analyses
Version: 0.1.0
Depends: R (>= 4.0.0), raster, terra,  rgbif, CoordinateCleaner, rgeos, mclust, ClusterR, FNN, geometry
Description: Workflow to generate taxa range maps from scratch based on ecoregions and an user-friendly GBIF wrapper (no hard-limit of < 100,000 species observations, filetring parameters to easily flag records, access to the GBIF backbone taxonomy)
License: GPL (>=3)
BugReports: https://github.com/8Ginette8/gbif.range/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Maintainer: Yohann Chauvier <yohann.chauvier@wsl.ch>
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
Authors: Yohann Chauvier [cre,aut] (https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9399-3192)
Collate:
    'make_tiles.R'
    'get_gbif.R'
    'get_taxonomy.R'
    'get_doi.R'
    'obs_filter.R'
    'get_range.R'
    'conv_function.R'

